HEADWORD: Demisuit
<hw>Dem"i*suit`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mil.
Antiq.)</fld> <def>A suit of light armor covering less than the whole
body, as having no protection for the legs below the thighs, no vizor to
the helmet, and the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Demit</ent>⟦br⟧
